Highway Accident Emergency Response Management System (HAERMS)
Web-Based Real-Time Emergency Coordination Platform
📘 COMPLETE PROJECT REPORT
(Ready for Final Year CSE / Smart City / TN Government Submission)

1️⃣ ABSTRACT
Highway accidents require immediate and coordinated response from police, ambulance, and hospitals. Delay in response time increases fatality risk.

The Highway Accident Emergency Response Management System (HAERMS) is a web-based real-time emergency coordination system that allows citizens to report accidents through a web SOS interface. The system automatically captures GPS location, assigns nearest police and ambulance units, alerts hospitals, and digitally manages the incident lifecycle until closure.

The system eliminates manual control room dependency and ensures:

Faster emergency response

Real-time communication

Automatic resource allocation

Digital incident logging

2️⃣ INTRODUCTION
India records a high number of highway accidents annually. Current challenges include:

Delay in response

Lack of real-time coordination

Manual dispatch inefficiencies

Poor hospital communication

HAERMS provides a centralized web-based real-time solution connecting:

Citizen → Police & Ambulance → Hospital → Incident Closed

3️⃣ PROBLEM STATEMENT
Traditional highway emergency systems suffer from:

Manual reporting delays

Lack of automated resource allocation

No real-time tracking

Poor hospital coordination

Paper-based logging

There is a need for a real-time automated web-based emergency response system.

4️⃣ OBJECTIVES
Develop a real-time web-based accident reporting system.

Automatically assign nearest police and ambulance.

Alert hospital based on severity.

Enable real-time dashboard updates.

Digitally log complete incident lifecycle.

Reduce emergency response time.

