Detailed Operational Procedures (Step-by-Step)
9.1 Citizen (SOS) Workflow
Access: Open the HERMS Public Portal on a mobile device.
Trigger: Use the "Shake to SOS" gesture or long-press the central SOS button.
Data Capture: The system captures high-accuracy GPS coordinates and activates the microphone/camera (if permitted).
Submission: The user confirms the emergency type (e.g., Accident, Medical).
Tracking: Upon submission, the user is redirected to a "Tracking" screen showing real-time ETA and positions of dispatched resources.
9.2 Patrol Unit Workflow
Availability: Login to the Patrol Dashboard and toggle status to 'AVAILABLE'.
Receipt: Receive an audible and visual "New Assignment" alert.
Acceptance: Review incident location and accept. Status auto-updates to 'EN ROUTE'.
Arrival: Upon reaching coordinates, click "ARRIVED ON SCENE". This notifies the control room and Citizen.
Action: Secure the area and provide initial situational data.
Resolution: Once the scene is clear, click "RESOLVED" to return to an 'AVAILABLE' state.
9.3 Ambulance Unit Workflow
Dispatch: Receive assignment based on proximity to the incident.
Navigation: Use the integrated Leaflet map for navigation to the specific GPS pin.
Assessment: On-scene, the crew enters patient triage data (Critical, Stable, etc.).
Hospital Selection: The system suggests the nearest hospital with available beds. The crew confirms the destination.
Transport: Clicking "START TRANSPORT" triggers a 'Field Alert' at the target hospital.
Handoff: Upon arrival at the ER, the hospital staff confirms admission, marking the ambulance as 'AVAILABLE'.
9.4 Hospital Workflow
Monitoring: Staff monitor the "Hospital Panel" for incoming field alerts.
Preparation: View patient vitals and ETA provided by the incoming ambulance crew.
Admission: When the ambulance arriving, click the "ADMIT" button for the specific incident.
Capacity: The system automatically decrements the 'Available Beds' count.
Administration: Staff can manually toggle "Hospital Full" status to prevent further auto-dispatches.
9.5 Administrator Oversight
Global View: Access the "Admin Dashboard" to see all active incidents across the state.
Direct Dispatch: Manually override auto-dispatch decisions if necessary.
Resource Analytics: Review response times and hospital utilization rates.
